   "source": [
    "# <center> Investigating a Chain of Interacting Beads</center>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$ \n"
    "  \\hspace{1in}\\displaystyle\n",
    "  F_{\\mathrm{FENE}}\\left(\\vec r\\right) = \\frac{3k_{\\mathrm{B}}T}{l_{\\mathrm{k}}} \\left( \n",
    "    \\frac{\\vec r /L_{\\mathrm{s}}}{1-{\\left(\\vec r/L_{\\mathrm{s}}\\right)^2}} \n",
    "  \\right)\n",
    "$ \n",
    "\n",
    "where $l_{\\mathrm{k}}$ is the Kuhn length and $L_{\\mathrm{s}}$ is the maximum spring length. The thermal energy is set to unity. The FENE force is just one of a few active forces;\n",
    "\n",
    "$ \\hspace{1in}\\displaystyle\n",
    "  \\sum F = F _{\\mathrm{random}} + F_{\\mathrm{FENE}} + F _{\\mathrm{excluded \\, volume}}\n",
    "$ \n",
    "\n",
    "where the excluded volume force is $+ k _{\\mathrm{excluded \\, volume}} \\left( r-r _\\jmath \\right)$, please note that this is the *interaction* force between each interacting pair of beads. This along with the other forces is used in the overdamped Langeving equation:\n",
    "\n",
    "$ \\hspace{1in}\\displaystyle\n",
    " \\dot {\\vec r} = \\dfrac{\\sum \\vec F}{b}\n",
    "$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from brownian_bead import *\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from scipy.optimize import curve_fit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generating $\\left\\langle{\\!R_\\mathrm{g}\\!}\\right\\rangle$ & $\\big\\langle{\\!R_\\mathrm{ee}\\!}\\big\\rangle$ Data\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from brownian_bead import *\n",
    "\n",
    "Δt = 0.001\n",
    "t = []\n",
    "tt = 0\n",
    "for i in range(N):\n",
    "    t.append(tt)\n",
    "    tt += Δt\n",
    "\n",
    "    \n",
    "print(\"now running simulation...\")\n",
    "sim = Simulation(nbeads=35)\n",
    "sim.advance(Δt, κ=1, κ_ev=1)     # κ_ev=0 for sanity check\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Ree = []\n",
    "for xy in end_to_end:\n",
    "    Ree.append(np.sqrt(xy[0]**2 + xy[1]**2))\n",
    "\n",
    "    \n",
    "print(\"...now writing to file\")   \n",
    "file = open(\"simulated_data/ave_rg_ree_n35.dat\", \"a\")\n",
    "for i, s in enumerate(Rg):\n",
    "\n",
    "    a = str( Rg[i] )\n",
    "    b = str( Ree[i] )\n",
    "    c = a + \" \" + b\n",
    "\n",
    "    file.write(c + '\\n')\n",
    "file.close()\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### importing and averaging"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "file = os.path.join('simulated_data', 'good_stuff', 'k=1...ls=1' 'ave_rg_ree_n100.dat')\n",
    "Rg_all = np.loadtxt(file, skiprows=0)[:, 0]\n",
    "Ree_all = np.loadtxt(file, skiprows=0)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "Rg_all_i = []\n",
    "Ree_all_i = []\n",
    "for i in range(N):\n",
    "    Rg_all_i.append([])\n",
    "    Ree_all_i.append([])\n",
    "    \n",
    "for i in range(int(len(Rg_all)/N)):   \n",
    "    for j in range(N):                 \n",
    "        Rg_all_i[j].append(Rg_all[j + i*N])\n",
    "        Ree_all_i[j].append(Ree_all[j + i*N])\n",
    "\n",
    "Rg_ave = []\n",
    "Ree_ave = []    \n",
    "for i in range(N):\n",
    "    Rg_ave.append(np.mean(Rg_all_i[i]))\n",
    "    Ree_ave.append(np.mean(Ree_all_i[i]))"
   ]
  },
